<br>
The only way i can get close (tri wield obviously gets me some victories, but on the 30 min timer, shouldnt have to use on lower levs should we...) is to not use any of our front load styles (ie. hurricane, fireblade, slam etc) as these all have medium penalty to defence &gt;&gt; and with our styles bonus damage coming nowhere close to alb/mid anytimes this does seem a huge hinderence for us. I have to try tactics and move a lot, and only use my reactive styles - that way i tend to parry/evade more often to get these off, although as u know no medium stun on even 3rd chain styles leaves us wanting again - and the main reason most bladies are respeccing to blunts to at least get a chance at stun, which can turn a fight.<br>
<br>
Of course i do enjoy working hard to get good performance outta my blademaster - but having played rangers/shades/champs - it is frustrating how badly we can get beaten, no other class i know can get as soundly beaten in a fight as my blademaster - even my pierce keen shade at lev 43 can score a bit of trouble on a lev 50 in open melee before getting downed, but a lev 50 blademaster has to rely on more luck and reactive styles than any other class in the game and this has to be wrong IMO. ( GOd i really hate moaning LOL but i just gotta speak out cause i want my blademaster to be a class that is NOT tittered at by all others on my realm).<br>
<br>
I've seen posts like mine appear all through the time i've played my baldey, and just hoped it would get better. I also understand MYTHIC must be against changing celtic dual cause it might make some rangers/shades overpowered - but shadowblades get LA and i wont begin on the rant about Shadowblades getting bigger hits, with faster weapons - after they have missed PA, sigh.<br>
<br>
But if anyone is interested i am compiling some logs, incl all manner of specced and RA boosted bladies and people can make judgements themselves, but if a ZERKER TEAMLEAD puts in his report that BMs and MERCS need help, it dont look good. I DONT wanna have to respecc to shield to be semi viable! <br>
<br>
Anyway, thats another whine about bladies! But it needs to be done...for gods sake i held aggro on Legion and parried him 10s of times in PvE then go RvR and get thumped/fried in 5 secs by a bloomin low lev skald. IF we get no more fixes, at least open some Blademaster stress management centres/ retirement homes please! thanks!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=addrick>Addrick</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(11/9/02 1:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> one of the problems i've noticed...</span><hr size=1>  I ran into a naked yellow con troll in Emain,<br>
